# DFHeadsMenu
a Diamondfire chunk o' code using the minecraft-heads API
Yes, I know a very impressive site.

--- How to Setup ---
! THIS REQURIES THE OVERLORD RANK !

1.Go into a creative singleplayer world with cheats enabled.
2.Give yourself a command block
3.Run this command:
<p class="code">/give @p player_head[minecraft:custom_name='{"italic":false,"text":"Head Menu"}',minecraft:custom_data={PublicBukkitValues: {"hypercube:codetemplatedata": "{\"author\":\"wodozar\",\"name\":\"Head Menu\",\"version\":1,\"code\":\"\"}"}}]</p>
4. Save the recieved item into your saved hotbars
5. Go onto your Diamondfire Plot and place the item in your codespace
6. Take out ender chests from the chest above the lapis block
7. Place the ender chests in your code space
8. Connect "ClickMenuSlot (MC-Heads)" to the ClickMenuSlot Player Event and "Command (MC-Heads)" to the Command Player Event
9. Setup complete

-- How to Use --
Using this is quite simple, just load into the game with /play and type in @heads, after this a menu should appear with the aviailable categories.
